    <note>He(2) Jingzhi [23380] See documentation in 1148 jinshi list, sijia #57, for great grandson, Teng [23383]. The family was established by Teng's great grandduncle. Jingzhi has the same generational name as all of He(2) Zhongli's [678] 11 sons. Jingzhi is not among them, but the zhi character could be a copying error for yuan, xian, or chu. In fact, Longping ji, 14.20a identifies a Jingshan as a son who is not listed in Zhongli's funerary inscription. I am going to assume that Jingzhi is a son of Zhongli, although he could be a nephew. I am also going to assume that the family moved to Hangzhou when Zhongli did, although Jingzhi could have moved to Kaifeng, but his immediate descendants probably moved to Hangzhou during the Southern Song.</note>
